  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to predict hemolysis in centrifugal blood pumps under ventricular assist device operating conditions. The CFD hemolysis model targets the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry and evaluates absolute hemolysis indices at physiologically relevant flow rates. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across blood viscosity, rotational speed, and inlet boundary conditions. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors were reviewed; seven were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps consistent with Model Risk Level 5 demands. Despite gaps, the overall credibility posture was deemed sufficient for the intended low-risk regulatory submission pathway under the Minimal profile declaration. No structured Context of Use object is bound to this unit; intended-use scope is conveyed narratively only.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-cfd-hemolysis-claim-001",
